Three Jubilee MPs have slammed Cord leader Raila Odinga for opposing the implementation of Sh6.8 billion Northern Collector Tunnel project that he launched when Prime Minister.Muthomi Njuki (Chuka Igambang'ombe) Kareke Mbiuki (Maara) and Tharaka Nithi woman representative Beatrice Nkatha said the opposition is not an expert to advise on the adverse environmental effects of the project.Read: Raila fights project he launched They spoke at Kirigi, Chuka Igambangombe during the launch of last mile electricity connection project spearheaded by Energy CS Charles Keter.Njuki disputed Raila claims that the project, funded by the World Bank, will be disastrous and will lead to desertification in Garissa, Ukambani Coast and Tana River delta."There is no way one person can fault everything that the Jubilee government wants to do to help Kenyans. He is pretending to know everything and is using the project to gain political mileage," Njuki said.Nkatha said Raila is against the project only because he wants wants kickbacks from the venture.Read: Raila using water project to gain political points, Wairia says, defends Jubilee